id: pm-pznn
title: Extract calendar UX into installable pm package
description: Move calendar/cal presentation toward an installable pm-calendar package while keeping deadline/reminder/event item metadata and core compatibility fallback intact.
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[5]: calendar,packages,pm-cli,refactor,sdk
created_at: "2026-05-14T06:05:23.346Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-14T07:31:20.886Z"
author: codex-agent
acceptance_criteria: pm-calendar package owns optional calendar UX; core keeps item deadline fields; contracts/MCP expose calendar commands only when package installed or during compatibility fallback; temp-project dogfood covers installed package behavior.
parent: pm-59gj
resolution: Extracted calendar presentation commands into the TypeScript-authored pm-calendar package and tightened static SDK contracts around package-owned actions.
expected_result: "pm-calendar installs as a first-party package, calendar/cal run through dynamic package handlers, static SDK actions exclude package-owned calendar/templates actions, and packed CLI smoke proves install/run/upgrade paths."
actual_result: "Focused tests, isolated dogfood, packed npx smoke, full coverage, required telemetry release gates, Sentry, and telemetry checks passed; validation has only the known pre-existing history drift warnings."
